CBRE, as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to present 9 Belmore Road, Randwick to the market.

The property is an outstanding mixed use retail and office investment in the highly demanded suburb of Randwick. With the Randwick Light Rail Station anticipated to provide strong growth prospects to the locality, the property is well placed to capitalise on the future upside.

9 Belmore Road, Randwick benefits from the following key attributes:

- Net income - $55,160.96*
- Zoning: B2 Local Centre
- Secure 3-year lease and 3-year option with EzyMart
- Well known Ground Floor tenant, EzyMart, which boasts over 200 stores nationwide
- The suburb projects high future growth with the construction of a new Light Rail Station
- Unrivalled location in the Randwick commercial precinct

The property will be offered for sale via public auction at AuctionWORKS, 50 Margaret Street, Sydney on Tuesday 27 June 2017 at 10:30am.

* Estimated fully leased gross income:$176,280pa*
* 3 x three-bedrooms
* 3 x two-bedrooms
* 2 x car parking spaces
* Strata Plan registered
* Zoned R3 - Medium Density Residential
* Land area 607sqm*
* Close proximity to public transport and amenities

"Under instructions from Jason Porter and Paul Weston of Pitcher Partners"

Auction: Tuesday 13 August 2013

CBRE, as the exclusive listing agent is pleased to present 2-10 Belmore Road, Randwick. The property is a fully let, North-East facing mixed use freehold building with significant development upside (STCA) 6.2km* from Sydney CBD. The site consists six boutique retail stores and a dance studio occupying the generous space upstairs, generating approximately $468,740* in gross annual rent. Enjoying 490sqm* total site area with rear pedestrian access, the property is opportunely situated on Randwicks main commercial thoroughfare, benefiting from high profile foot traffic through surrounding infrastructure and local amenity including hospitals, schools, education, and shopping centres.   

Belmore Road is positioned to capitalise on the dense population immediately generated from two shopping centres, Prince of Wales hospital, Sydney Children's hospital, and University of New South Wales all within 1km*.    

2-10 Belmore Road, Randwick benefits from the following key attributes:

Fully let to seven established and popular tenants
North-East facing mixed use freehold building with development upside (STCA) 
Large site area of 490sqm* with rear street access
Ideally positioned in the centre of Randwicks main commercial hub, only 6.2km* from Sydney CBD
High exposure corner location with dual street frontages to Belmore Road (28m*) and Alison Road (7.5m*)
Height of building limit of 12 metres.
Floor space ratio of 2:1
B2 Local centre zoning

2-10 Belmore Road, Randwick will be sold via an Expressions of interest campaign closing on Wednesday 14th of July 2021 at 4:00pm.  

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approx.
